True of all ramp tho and people still run it

I meant in terms of it being better for low CMC generals vs other.

Thus it’s more narrow than other Moxen, but that doesn’t make it strictly bad.

Mox Amber probably also scales w the game and thus gets better. I would guess that as the years pass the density of legendaries in the 99 has increased. Obviously you get stuff like walkers becoming legendary which boosts that number, but with each set you get more choices. How many good walkers worth putting in a deck were there RtR and prior? Compare that to since then. Dovan Baan would have been in a ton of EDH decks had he been from Alara. He's a really solid card compared to Chandra Ablaze or something, but now a days he's barely remarked upon in EDH.
Equipment decks are now running Balan, Sram, and Danitha just from the last couple of years
Once upon a time I had no other legendary creatures in Glissa. Now I have Gonti, Rhonas, mono-b Sidisi, Tetzimoc and Gitrog Monster
So assuming that trend continues at lest a little you'll see Mox Amber get more and more playable
